  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "QAQC Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:-</strong></p><p>-Conduct QAQC daily checks<br />-Prepare monthly QAQC report for submission to Corporate QAQC Department<br />-Conducting monthly QAQC Training to Sub-contractors<br />-Issuance of QAQC Non-compliance to sub-contractors<br />-Attend monthly QAQC presentation and meeting at Corporate QAQC Department<br />-Conduct regular inspections to ensure works are in compliance with method statements (in accordance to BCA’s Good Industry Practice & approval from the clients and consultants)<br />-Arrange and liaise with BCA for CONQUAS/QM assessments. Act as the primary quality liaison with clients and consultants, updating them on QA/QC matters and addressing quality concerns directly related to CONQUAS scoring.<br />-Work closely with site engineers and supervisors to ensure construction methods comply with CONQUAS specifications, providing guidance on quality protocols and rectifications or even conducting relevant training as needed.<br /></p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>-Architectural-trained or Structural-trained work experience<br />-Min 3 years experience as a QAQC Engineer in A1 building main construction company, with added experience in managing Quality Marks assessment processes or certifications a significant advantage<br />-Able to communicate effectively and clearly<br />-Able to work independently, be meticulous, analytical with excellent problem-solving skills, proactive & able to meet tight deadlines<br />-Good knowledge of construction quality control/assurance is necessary<br />-Certifications: BCA-Approved CONQUAS training or relevant quality certification such as ISO 9001:2015 in Quality Management Systems.</p>",
